Here's someone right now who is fixing my kitchen floor. And I'm pretending right now that I still have a job and am working from home while I sit on Too Hot to Handle.
If I could damn well open the file. (Shit One Drive.)
*Hackers voice* I'm in.
And that's when he starts drilling really loudly. Hurrah.
It feels uncomfortably passive-aggressive to turn my air purifier all the way up, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would actually be completely okay even if he weren't a mask opponent. And do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he leaves.
At least I finally finished revising chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damn terrifying. Oh yeah, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing search and replace for … ➡️ ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I stick to my decision. Natural language is usually choppy, especially when you get emotional.
The contractor is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he'll be done soon.
He went out to cut something (at least that's what it sounds like). I secretly checked how far he was. There's still a lot to do :(
7 more pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's quite tidy – mainly changes to the text and very minor corrections in direct speech, and I need to make everything a bit more concise. But I could really use a break and a tea right now, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he's just started vacuuming dust again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me that he had done a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were too cheap and only paid for the part next to the door that wasn't in order anymore. Feels so much better now.
The house is being ventilated and my air purifier is running in the kitchen, while I drink tea in the garden!
